   Welcome to Physicians and Surgeons Licensing System

   The On-line Professional Licensing System enables Physicians and
   Surgeons to renew their license, request duplicate licenses, and make
   address changes. Also, first-time applicants may begin the initial
   application process.

   You are eligible to renew online if:
     * Your license is in active or inactive status.
     * Your license expires within the next 4 months.
     * Your license is delinquent by no more than 90 days.
     * You have completed your Continuing Medical Education.

              The following credit cards are accepted:
               VISA, MASTERCARD, DISCOVER
        ** There is a $10 convenience fee added to each renewal or initial
   application transaction that requires a payment.

   FIRST TIME USERS -  You will need your:
     * License Number (for renewals) Example (alpha/numeric = G12345)
     * Social Security Number
     * Credit Card Information
     * eMail Address   -   Very important that you enter a correct email
       address   - Example ( jsmith@aaa.com )
     * Click here to get started, or click on Professional Licensing link
       in left column.

   RETURNING USERS -   You will need your:
     * User ID
     * Password
     * Credit Card Information
     * Click here to get started, or click on Professional Licensing link
       in left column.

   Additional Documentation:
   Requests for duplicate licenses and for first-time licensure will
   require supporting documentation be mailed to the Medical Board.
   The requested forms may be downloaded and printed. All forms are
   available at www.medbd.ca.gov. In the left menu column click the "Forms
   & Publications" link, then click the Physician and Surgeon Forms and
   Materials link.

   For assistance in the on-line process you may contact the Department of
   Consumer Affairs eGovernment Team at (916) 322-7834 between the hours
   of 8-5 PST Monday through Friday, or email to egov@dca.ca.gov.
   For licensing information you may contact the Medical Board of
   California at (916) 263-2382.
   If you are a AOL user please read AOL User Browser Requirements here or
   on left menu bar.


